This Button EXITs the Editor. You are now in the Mainscreen.

This Button allows you to TEST your currently edited level. Scores that are
made in Testingmode are not archived in the TOP-HUNDRED Scoreboard. Press
`ESC` to exit Testmode and to return to the Editor.

With this Button you may load a `TRIZ.Levels` File.

This Button is to make your edited Levels saved. Saving a File named
`TRIZ.Levels` means that this file will be loaded on Startup.

This Button shows if the Next upcomig Block will be shown or not.

This Button shows if the Blocks will apear Random Rotated or not.

This Button shows if all Joystickactions are Reversed or not.

This Button gives you the ability to restore the Default Levels.

This Button will clear the Playfield.

With this Button you select the Level you wish to edit.

With this Button you select how many Lines (up to 99) have to build to solve
the level.

This Button will add a level (up to 99).

This Button will delete the last Level.

This Button will edit the playingspeed. The current speed is shown above.
Remember that this value is the amount of waitingtime, meaning increasing
the Speedvalue will give less speed.

RND BLOCKS are Blocks wich will be displayed somewere on the screen during
play. This will add the player some trouble. The amount of Blocks is shown
above. This value means the amount of lines beeing used for displaying the
Blocks. Set this value to zero for no RND BLOCKS.

By pressing inside the Playfield you are able to set Blocks, which will be
displayed after a level began.



You can have a look at the Scoreboard by moving the Joystick down while you
are in the Mainscreen. Then you are able to scroll around moving the
Joystick up and down.




